# Architecture Rules

## System Layers

This repo has two layers:

1. **OS Layer** — `docs/`, `agents/`, `templates/`, `scripts/`
2. **Application Layer** — `src/` + `app/`

## Clean Architecture (`src/`)

```
presentation → application → domain ← infrastructure
```

| Layer | Responsibility | May depend on |
|-------|----------------|---------------|
| presentation | UI, hooks, view composition | application, domain (read) |
| application | Use cases, orchestration | domain |
| domain | Entities, rules, repository interfaces | nothing external |
| infrastructure | API, DB, external services | domain (implements interfaces) |

**Dependency rule**: dependencies point inward. Domain must not import frameworks or DB libraries.

## `app/` vs `src/`

- `app/` — Next.js routes, layouts, Server/Client entry points only
- `src/` — all business logic, reusable UI, use cases
- Route Handlers call `src/application/` — no business logic in `app/`

## Directory Map

- `docs/context/` — background and constraints
- `docs/plan/` — design before implementation
- `docs/build/` — implementation and deployment records
- `agents/` — agent roles and handoff rules

## Changes

- Read `ARCHITECTURE.md` before structural changes
- New layers or cross-boundary imports require a Plan in `docs/plan/`
- Technology choices must align with `TECH_STACK.md`
- Prefer reuse (`templates/`, existing modules) over rewrite

## Next.js 16

Consult `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` and `AGENTS.md` — APIs differ from older Next.js versions.
